All Classes

Class Summary 
Class Description
Account
Class representing the GUI that shows the user their account page
ChangePass
Class representing the GUI to change the user's account password
Client
Class to handle the client side of the socket connection between a client and the server
ClientAcct
Abstract class to represent each account with each username, password, balance, unique ID, transaction list, and friend list for each account
CompanyAccount
Class that represents the GUI that appears when the user is making a company account
CompanyAcct
Class that handles company accounts
CreateAccount
Class representing the GUI to create a new account
Flag
Class to represent flags that are sent between the client and server to represent errors
IndividualAcct
Class that handles accounts for individuals
LoginInfo
Method representing serializable login information for an account
Main
Class that runs the GUIs and creates a client connection to communicate the information entered into the GUI to the server
Packet
Method to represent a serializable packet of information that can be sent through a connection
Pay
Class representing the GUI to make a payment
Request
Class representing the GUI when a payment request is being made
Server
Connections.Server class which will be used to talk to clients and query
SignIn
Class representing the sign in page when the user first starts the program to log in to an account
TestSERVER
Class to run the server to communicate between the client and the database
Transaction
Class that contains information for each transaction
Type
Class representing the GUI that appears when the user is creating an account and needs to specify which type of account to create (company or individual)
